entry.title: VEA's RequestEncodingParametersChange allows frame size change.
entry.content:
This CL updates the signature of VEA's RequestEncodingParametersChange

to support frame size change. It adds a new parameter |size| for the new

visible frame size.



This CL doesn't add the frame size support either VEA or VEA client. It

will be added in a follow up CL. Not all VEAs are going to support this

feature. Query |VideoEncoderInfo.supports_frame_size_change| before

requesting frame size change.



Design doc: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QtGs7lEbXuRqAub3GxouuuvNsKpDtHzFcHkGQnnAC0c/edit?usp=sharing

entry.title: CHECK failure with MathML + ::first-letter
entry.content:
Ensure that display: math elements handle ::first-letter the same as

flexbox/grid in order to fix a CHECK failure. display: math elements do

not support linebreaking, so an equivalent testcase for ::first-line

is not possible. The WG is agreeing about whether these pseudo-elements

entry.title: [DownloadBubble] Remove V2 feature flag
entry.content:
This removes the base::Feature for kDownloadBubbleV2. The feature has

been launched in its V2 form, so this removes any code that is active

in a non-V2 state, and changes all checks of the V2 feature state to be

equivalent to "true".



In particular, this removes the checkbox from the security view.



This also slightly modifies the logic for ephemeral warnings. Previously

the "don't do this if the download bubble v2 isn't enabled" logic was

handled by treating all downloads as "not ephemeral warnings" if bubble

v2 was not enabled. Now, we treat them as ephemeral warnings, but only

schedule the cancellation of ephemeral warnings if the download bubble

is enabled. This makes the behavior more consistent and easier to reason

about across platforms.



Bug: 1504207

entry.title: [lacros] Delay SkiaOutputSurfaceImplOnGpu::MakeCurrent() calls when appropriated
entry.content:
It was verified that calls to SkiaOutputSurfaceImplOnGpu::MakeCurrent()

take place needlessly in case no GL or fence operations were performed.

A clear example scenario is playing videos in fullscreen mode (eg

on youtube).



In lacros, those calls are being scheduled by

SkiaOutputSurfaceImpl::SwapBuffers(), and ultimately called out by

SkiaOutputSurfaceImpl::FlushGpuTasksWithImpl().

In practice, the needless calls to MakeCurrent() might take a non

trivial time to perform (ranging from ~15us to ~90us!), possibly

influencing both power consumption and performance itself.



This CL is a first attempt to reduce the number of needless

MakeCurrent() calls in lacros. It is possible that similar approach is

also extended to other platforms, including ChromeOS.



On an atlas chromeos device, the following command was used to gather

any measurable difference in power consumption with this approach:



$ dump_intel_rapl_consumption --repeat --interval_ms=1000;



Although the intervals used to gather the data are not long (samples of

5, 10 and 15 minutes long), the outcome produced some interesting results

that credence the CL for a most robust measurement, using Chrome infra tools.

entry.title: Fix Lacros ephemeral windows crash during restore
entry.content:
On debug builds, ChromeOS will crash on a DCHECK during restore if an

ephemeral was open during restore.



These windows a default app_restore::kWindowIdKey of 0, and therefore

have a 0 as browser_session_id.



Additionally, many ephemral windows, such as Isolated Web Apps

installer, do not want to be restored. So in this CL, we abort saving if

browser_session_id is 0.

entry.title: [X11] Cache WM state in Connection
entry.content:
With this change a round-trip is no longer necessary when checking

if the WM supports a feature. WmSupportsHint is a low-level function

that's called often (eg on every mouse move in the non-client area),

so this should reduce a lot of round trips. Additionally, the WM

state was stored in a static variable before, which will break if

a window manager starts or stops (which is supported in X11) while

Chrome is running. This CL fixes that issue.



R=sky
